inn1.comm: starts off with a good length delivery on the middle and off stump line, Sehwag on the back-foot defending.

good length delivery, drifting down the leg side, Sehwag fails to make contact, ball clips the pad and rolls away behind square on the leg side, fielders are deep and a quick single is taken - India off the mark
on the middle and off stump line, excellent line and length first-up, Dravid gets well forward and defends it away towards cover
short of a good length delivery, pitched in line and angling across, no movement whatsoever, Dravid reads it well and leaves it through to the keeper
another good delivery from Bravo, on the stumps and Dravid watchfully strokes it back to the bowler

and Bradshaw strikes! good length delivery on the middle and off stump line, this one shaped back in after hitting the deck, Dravid is sucked forward into the drive, ball swings in just enough to beat the inside edge and Dravid is trapped plumb in front, dead as a stone!
short and wide outside the off stump, in the slot for Sehwag and he hammers it over the fielder at point,. Sehwag off the mark in typical fashion - its a no-ball aswell
on the stumps, forced away on the leg side and they scamper through for a single
played wide of the fielder at mid-off
good length delivery, shaping away and Sehwag is beaten outside the off stump, well bowled Edwards
wicket to wicket delivery, Sehwag drives off the front-foot, not a well timed shot, ball clips the inner half of the bat and rolls back to the bowler
pitched up outside the off stump, bit awyward and moving away, Sehwag leaves it through to the keeper, close to being called a wide, infact it looked like a wide but Edwards gets away with it
on the middle and leg stump line, salnting in, Sehwag drives off the back-foot and the ball rolls down to mid-on
good length delivery outside the off stump, no shot offered
good length delivery on the middle and off stump line, defended down on the off side
driven away towards towards cover, good shot for no run
another good delivery from Bradshaw, defended watchfully
good length delivery, close to the off stump line, again no movement in the air or off the track, Raina shuffles forward and across and drives it straight to Chanderpaul at mid-off
another decent delivery, Raina once again finds Chanderpaul at mid-off, end of a good over
slightly short and slanting in, that's his stock delivey, Sehwag gets behind the line and plays it away towards cover point
short of a good length delivery, again slanting in from outside the off stump, Sehwag is beaten by the extra pace and the ball hits his high on the pad, half-hearted appeal for lbw turned down

short rising delivery outside the off stump, excellent effort ball, Sehwag gets under the bounce looking to lift it down to third man, the upper-cut as they call it but on this occasion he fails to make contact and the ball thuds into the keeper's gloves
on the middle and leg stump line, Sehwag quickly shuffles back and clips it away well wide of the fielder at square leg, dangerous shot - miss and you are plumb!
good length delivery outside the off stump, driven on the up and the ball goes right into the gap between cover and point, out filed slows the ball down and the fielder catches up
short ball, defended on the back-foot and the ball rolls back to the bowler, well bowled and well played
good length delivery, driven away well wide of the man at mid-on
short of a good length delivery, angling across the right-hander, Sehwag leans back and steers it down to third man for a single
pitched up outside the off stump, Raina pushes forward to the pitch of the delivery and handsomely drives it past the fielder at cover, sweetly timed and the placement was even better!
four more! good length delivery, drifting onto middle and leg and Raina clips it away through midwicket for yet another boundary, India on the move now.
off the pads to the square leg region
cut away late to the third man region, easy single to end the over
full and on the stumps, worked to the leg side, off the inside edge to the on side
good length ball outside the off, driven though cover
short ball, down the leg side, Sehwag gets inside the line and tucks it down to fine leg
defended on the front foot
bang! short and wide outside the off stump, Sehwag stays back and murders it over the backwards point fence, typical
good length delivery outside the off stump, glided down to third man for an easy single, excellent over so far for India
edged away towards point
short rising delivery, angled in from outside the off stump, Sehwag battled hard to avoid it, awkward looking defensive shot and the ball pops up on the off side
on the pads, clipped away through square leg for an easy single
driven wide of the cover fielder, excellent shot
better line and lenght, driven away towards mid-off
on the pads, driven well wide of the fielder at midwicket

shot! good length delivery, close to the off stump line and slanting across, Raina gets a good stride forward to the pitch of the delivery and jabs it away right into the hole between mid-off and cover, fantastic shot
full ball on the off stump, Sehwag waits ont he ball and pushes it through the off side at the last moment for a single
fullish and outside the off, Raina drives towards point but cannot beat the fielder
again quite full and on the stumps, Raina drives nicely, getting his foot to the pitch of the ball but he can only find the fielder at mid off
Bang! That was just a touch too wide to Sehwag, he launches into a big drive and the ball booms away through cover for a boundary. That is more like the Sehwag we know!
fuller and on the stumps, just pushed to the fielder at cover with an angled bat
Another big one! Full and a touch too straight and Sehwag lines the ball up and clatters it back over the bowler's head for a boundary!
fullish ball on the stumps, played away to the off side
good length delivery on the off stumps, Sehwag angles the bat and runs the ball through the point region for a single
punched away to the off side but Raina can't beat the infield and there's no chance of a run
short of a good length and outside the off, Raina shapes to cut but can't get hold of it and the ball goes off the inside edge down to the keeper

short of a driving length and outside the off, the ball angles away towards the slips, Raina goes for the big shot and plays it well, driving on the up, the placement is good and there's no chance at all for the fielder
punched to cover, that ends a good over for India
steered down to third-man for an easy single

good-length ball on the stumps, Raina goes to work the ball to the on side but that's a dangerous ploy. He misses and Bradshaw is right on the money! Raina has to take a walk as the stumps are shattered! West Indies have their second wicket and it's a big one as Raina had been batting handsomely.
short of a good length and outside the off stump, Kaif watches it carefully and leaves it well alone to the keeper
good length ball, just outside the off, Kaif gets behind the line and defends
short of a driving length and on the off, Kaif goes back and across and plays a forcing shot towards cover
that's a good shot. Kaif waits on the ball, sees there's a bit of width on it and eases it through cover
short of a length and outside the off, Sehwag neatly tucks the ball down to the third-man region for a single
fuller and on the stumps, Kaif is more circumspect than Sehwag and just defends with a straight bat back towards the on side
on the pads this time and Kaif can work the ball away down towards square-leg for a single
short one banged in, Sehwag goes for the pull, it's not a shot he plays especially well, the ball bobs off to the on side off the top half of the bat
Bang! short and too much width, Sehwag undercuts this one well over the man at point! Sehwag loves to play that shot and certainly hits it well
eased down to third-man for a single  to end the over
slightly short and outside the off stump, Sehwag punches well but can only find the man at cover
another single pinched to the third-man area, it's Sehwag this time who steers the ball away
full and on the stumps, driven down to the man at mid off, no chance of a run
short of a driving length and outside the off stump, Kaif leaves this well alone, Carlton Baugh who is standing up to the stumps takes the ball smartly
short of a length and outside the off, eased to cover
tidy line and length from the industrious Bradshaw, defended and that brings us to the end of this over
fullish and on the stumps, sehwag tries to work the ball away back down the pitch but gets a bit tangled up and the ball ends up at his feet
just a little width, just a fraction short and Sehwag waits late on the ball to play a superb cut shot. The timing and placement are perfect and the ball races away to the fence!
short one banged in, Sehwag goes for the hook, he's not at all in control and the ball goes off the top edge, over the keeper, one bounce and into the advertising hoardings at fine-leg!
short of a length and outside the off, Sehwag shapes to cut but can't quite get hold of it, the ball bobs off to the off side
slower one, Sehwag picks it and slices it away down to the third-man fence! That is a stylish, controlled shot and brings up a half-century for Sehwag!
short of a good length and on the off, Kaif stands tall and punches the ball towards the fielder at cover
again short of a length and on the leg stump, worked away to the on side
slightly short, Kaif picks the length early and plays a short-arm jab, he keeps the ball down well and gets four
fullish and drifting down leg, Kaif whips it to the on side well but Runako Morton dives at square-leg and half stops the ball
fuller and on the stumps, punched to mid off
fullish and outside the off, driven edgily down to third man for a single to end the over
full and flat, defended back down the pitch to the bowler
again quite flat and on the stumps, worked to the leg side
single pinched as the ball is on the pads and Kaif can work the ball through square-leg
tucked away to the on side, just wide of Lara at midwicket for a single
short and a bit of width, cut played but the ball goes straight to the fielder at short third-man
short of a length and on the off, Kaif whips the ball to the leg side but cannot beat the man at midwicket. He's struggling a bit here with his placement
fuller and on the pads, this time Kaif can work the ball away far enough from the fielder at square-leg and will pick up a couple of runs
short one banged in! A bit of pace and bounce there. Kaif wants none of it and ducks well under the ball
slightly short of a length and on the off stump, Kaif plays the pull but not quite convincingly and the ball rolls down towards midwicket, a single is stolen
short one banged in again. Good pace and carry, the ball flies over Sehwag's shoulders and goes through to the keepera
fullish and outside the off, driven towards cover where Sarwan dives and half stops the ball
this one is placed and timed immaculately! Just too much width and Sehwag strokes the ball away magnificently to the cover fence to bring up the hundred!
full and on the off, pushed to cover
driven into the outfield for a couple more
dabbed down towards short third-man for a single
punched to the on side but not past the man at midwicket
short of a length and on the pads, worked away down to the man at fine-leg for a single
another short one but this is misdirected and far outside the off stump, Sehwag leaves it well alone and it is called a wide
shortish ball, punched towards cover
another short one banged in, this time slipping down the leg side, Kaif leaves it well alone to the keeper
full this time and on the off, Kaif drives well towards cover where Lara misfields and the batsmen pick up a single
again short and too wide, Sehwag slashes at it but cannot reach it and that is easily called a wide
slower ball, well picked up, Sehwag dabs the ball to the off side and scrambles a single that brings up the fifty partnership
fullish and on the off, defended with soft hands, quick single run as the ball goes away towards the off side
this one's dropped down a bit short and slips away past the bat down the leg side, wide called
and another wide! Again down leg, won't get away with that in one-day cricket
slightly short of a length and on the stumps, played at and missed, the ball goes over the stumps to the keeper
clipped to the on side
full and straight, played back to the bowler
eased down to long on for a single
another easy single picked off and that's the end of the over
short of a good length delivery outside the off stump, ball stayed a bit low after hitting the deck, Sehwag goes for the late cut and gets beaten by the lack of bounce, bit of a lazy shot that
bit wide outside the off stump and Sehwag strokes it away well wide of the fielder at point
good length delivery on the middle and leg stump line, excellent pick up shot from Kaif but the ball finds the fielder at midwicket

goodness me! wayward  delivery down the leg side and keeper had no chance of cutting it off, full length dive from Baugh ends in vain and the ball races away to the fine leg fence - five more added to the total!
good length delivery outside the off stump, defended towards point, no room for a single there

good length delivery outside the off stump, Kaif slices it away in the air and straight to the fielder at third man, the ball was in the air for a long time but fell well short of the fielder in the deep
Edwards continues to struggle, another horrible delivery down the leg side but this time Baugh had it covered
good length delivery, on the stumps and cutting in, Sehwag ends up with an inside edge and the ball rolls away behind point, stifled appeal for lbw turned down
fuller and on the stumps, played straight back to the bowler
flatter delivery, Kaif pushes forward and taps it away well wide of the fielder at cover
fuller outside the off stump, Sehwag waits for the bat and at the last moment runs it down to short third man, fielder moves across quickly and negates a chance of a single
defended down on the off side, played with soft hands and a quick single is taken
good length delivery outside the off stump, Sehwag reads it well and drives it away through cover point for an easy single
driven wide of the fielder at mid-on

quicker delivery, drifting onto middle and leg, Sehwag looking to whip it away through midwicket fails to make contact, ball hits the pad and rolls away towards point, quick single called for but Kaif stands his ground, bit of a mix-up but Sarwan moving in from the edge of the circle fails to hit the stumps at the striker's end, direct hit would have been interesting!
on the pads, Kaif has a whip at it  but makes no contact, ball clips the pad and rolls away on the leg side
another good length delivery, again on the middle and leg stump line, Kaif stays back and neatly drives it away through midwicket, runs hard and comfortably comes back for the second
played just wide of the fielder at mid-on, risky single
eased away on the leg side
driven wide of the fielder at cover
steered away straight to the fielder at short third man
forced away through cover point, yet another easy single added to the total
fraction short and turning in, Kaif stands tall on the back-foot and punches it down to long-on
quicker delivery, drifting down the leg side and rightly called a wide
on the stumps, punched off the back-foot and once again the ball races away through mid-on

oopsy-daisy! good length delivery on the middle and off stump line, Sehwag stands his ground and swings hard, ball hits the middle of the bat and flies over the wide long-on fence, longest boundary on the ground but Sehwag cleared it with ease, amazing shot
flicked away off the pads to deep square leg, this is good cricket
on the pads, Bravo struggling a bit here, Kaif too neatly tucks it away through square leg for an easy single
again turned away off the pads, this time behind square for a single
better line and length, played straight to the fielder at midwicket
fuller length delivery outside the off stump, driven away to deep cover for a single, not an aggressive shot - just a punch
comes down the track to the pitch of the delivery and drives it down long-off
slightly short and turning in, Sehwag drives off the back-foot and gets it away to deep cover
quicker delivery outside the off stump, no shot offered
forced away towards short cover, quick single taken

MAX! fuller length delivery, on the middle and off stump line, Sehwag steps forward and lofts it over the long-on fence for his third six of the innings - there was a fielder in the deep but Sehwag cleared him comfortably
played back to the bowler, Gayle starts off with an expensive over
worked away off the pads for an easy single
short and wide outside the off stump, was there to be cut but Sehwag finds the fielder at point, missed out there on some easy runs

well disguised slower delivery, Sehwag on the front-foot driving and the ball zips past the outside edge, beaten comprehensively by the clever change of pace - this is arguably the best ball bowled by Bravo so far
driven wide of the fielder at mid-off
good length delivery, close to the off stump, Kaif gets into a good position and drives it wide of the fielder at cover
turned away towards short fine leg, quick single to end the over
eased down to long on
full and on the stumps, Kaif pushed the ball down to long on for a single, the second of the over in as many balls
fullish and outside the off, driven through cover for yet another single
just short of a length and on the pads, picked away through square-leg and you know the rest
short of a good length and outside the off, Sehwag goes back and cuts past point, five singles so far
Kaif can't get this away and guides the ball straight to short third-man

slower ball, on the stumps, Sehwag half sweeps the ball to the leg side for a single to the sweeper on the fence
&
fuller length delivery on the middle and off stump line, Kaif jams his bat down in time and flicks it away to wide long-on for a single
Fullish and outside the off, Sehwag slashes hard at the ball and it races away off a thickish outside edge, past the keeper and too fine for the fielder at third-man! Sehwag moves to 96!

And Bravo strikes back for the home team and that is the wicket West Indies wanted! A full delivery, swings in late, probably reverse swing, Sehwag comes forward to drive but  is struck full on the boot, loud shout for the lbw rightly upheld by umpire Asad Rauf, India three down.
off the mark straightaway, fullish and outside the off stump, Dhoni squeezes that off a thick outside edge past short third-man for a couple
full and on the off, just a touch of swing into Dhoni who pushes the ball firmly to mid off off the front foot
short and on the off, Dhoni half cuts half drives to the off side
flat and on the stumps, Dhoni tries to work the ball to the leg side, off the leading edge to the off side
once again flat and straight, off the pad down to the on side
fuller and on the leg stump, worked away for a single
full and on the off, eased to long on for a single to end the over
short and a bit of width, cut down to the man at point
short and wide, Kaif plays a big hit towards cover but cannot beat Chris Gayle at short cover
full and outside the off stump, Kaif drives through cover for a single
fuller this time and on the stumps, driven down to long-on for a single
just short of a good length and on the pads, clipped to midwicket
punched down to the on side, past the bowler for a single
just short of a length and a touch short, Kaif goes back and eases that one beautifully through cover, they run hard and can come back for a third run
short ball on the stumps, whipped to the on side
again shipped away, this time wide of the man at midwicket
short of a length and on the pads, clipped to the leg side
on the pads and very full, flicked down to fine-leg for a single
flat and on the pads, worked down to square-leg
too full and down the leg side, Kaif works the ball away off his hips past the man at short fine-leg for a boundary!
full and on the pads, worked to midwicket
full and very straight, Kaif tries to work the ball to the leg side but only gets a leading edge, the ball bobs up towards Samuels at cover who runs in and dives but cannot complete the catch
full-toss, could have gone anywhere but Dhoni hits it straight to mid-off
BANG! Dhoni winds up and tees off. He smashes that over mid-off, one bounce and over the ropes. That is a top shot!
full and straight, played back down the pitch
full and on the pads, flicked away to the on side just far enough away from the fielder for the batsmen to steal a single
defended back down the pitch
full and on the pads, worked away to the on side for a quick single
short of a length and on the off, Kaif has time to go back and drive the ball to long off for a single
full and straight, scooped down to the on side
flatter, faster, on the leg stump and slipping further down, flick played and missed, through to the keeper
fullish and quite straight, Kaif gets behind the line nicely and punches to off
short of a good length and outside the off, Kaif drives but the timing is off and the ball just dribbles past cover
short of a length and on the stumps, Dhoni dabs the ball away past the bowler, down to long-on for a single
fullish and on the stumps, flicked away down towards long-on for a single
short of a length and a bit of width outside the off, Dhoni goes back and cuts well for a single
fullish and on the stumps, worked to the leg side for a single to get the over going
very full and quite straight, worked away through the leg side for an easy single
short of a length and on the stumps, worked to the leg side and a quick first run allows the batsmen to come back for a second
flat and on the stumps, worked to midwicket
this time full and on the stumps and Kaif flicks but cannot beat the field
flat and straight, again Kaif struggles to get the ball past the infield
fullish and on the leg stump, worked down to the man at short fine-leg
speared in on the pads, Dhoni squeezes the ball away to the on side for a single
again full and very straight, Kaif just eases the ball to long-on for a single
full and on the pads, dabbed down to short fine-leg
once again very flat and very straight, defended to cover
this one is on the pads and Dhoni can ease the ball past the man at short fine-leg for a single

Dhoni drives a full one hard towards Gayle who dives and half stops the ball. The batsmen set off for a quick single. Gayle recovers quickly, scoops up the ball and fires the throw in on the stumps. Dhoni is a bit lax getting back and could be in trouble. Bucknor refers it to the third umpire and after many replays the decision, a close one, is that Dhoni is short of his crease!
slightly short, quite quick, Kaif chops to short third-man
eased through cover for a single
short of a length and outside the off, defended carefully
short of a length and outside the off, chopped down to the keeper
fuller and straighter, defended carefully back down the pitch
full and flat, defended back down the pitch to the on side, the bowler fields
eased down to fine-leg
again very flat and full, played back to the bowler
flat and on the pads, defended to the leg side
fuller and outside the off, driven on the up, in the air to long off
flatter and spinning a touch, defensive shot played and missed, struck on the pad

played with an angled bat to short third-man, Chanderpaul runs in quickly, one handed pick up and throw, Baugh whips off the bails, Kaif dives, his bat is over the line of the crease but in the air and that is another run out!
full and on the off, Pathan comes forward and defends
flat and on the pads, Rao flicks wide of square-leg for a single
single eased down to long-on
and another slightly short, straight ball is worked down to long-on for a single

slightly short, the ball grips the surface and stops on the batsman, Pathan plays a half-hearted shot and pops the simplest of catches back to Marlon Samuels! West Indies have done superbly to peg India back!
full and outside the off, defended
and once again Powar defends watchfully to end the over
worked away through square-leg
another quick run through square-leg
quick, flat ball, played at and missed, through to the keeper
pushed towards cover
played to short third-man
cut past cover-point
fullish and on the pads, Powar sweeps and misses and is bowled round his legs! That is an inspired bowling change from Brian Lara!
full and on the stumps, played back to the bowlers
tossed up and outside the leg stump, Agarkar uses his feet and chips to the leg side
full and on the off, driven to cover
tossed up and on the off, defended towards the off side
driven back to the bowler
flat and on the off, defended back down the pitch
just drifting down leg and worked away towards the on side
punched back past the bowler to long off for a single
full and on the off stump, pushed towards the man at cover, single pinched
short of a length and on the pads, worked to the leg side
good-length ball on the off, steered to short third-man
on the pads and flat, worked to the leg side
another quick single as the ball is defended to the leg side
and once again all the batsman can do is dab the ball to the leg side and scamper a quick single
full and down the leg side, flick played and missed, through to the keeper, it's wide and a bye
full and on the off, a hint of reverse swing, punched through cover

full ball on the off stump, Agarkar digs it out and drives straight. Too straight and the ball hits the stumps at the non-striker's end. Fidel Edwards fields and can't believe his luck as Agarkar has charged down the pitch for a single. Venugopala Rao responds very late and the throw lobs to the keeper and he is easily run out!
full and straight, attempted yorker, dug out towards short third-man
fullish and on the stumps, punched to long-on for a single
full and on the stumps, it's a slower ball, well bowled, defended watchfully by Harbhajan
another slower ball, Harbhajan flicks, off the leading edge into no man's land just back past the bowler
full and outside the off stump, driven to cover
again straight and quite full, defended to the leg side
fullish but drifting onto the pads, whipped away through square-leg for a brace
full and straight, worked to the leg side
full and on the stumps, dug out towards the man at cover
just the single as a full ball is swatted to the on side
full and straight, driven inside out to the man at cover
full and on the pads, turned away through square-leg for yet another single
full and on the pads, squeezed to the on side. Just one over left in the innings now
slower ball, just outside the off, Harbhajan has a swipe and misses, through to the keeper
yet another slower one, again a massive heave that misses, through to the keeper
GONE! Yet another slower ball from Bravo and Agarkar's attempted big hit only goes up in the air and to Brian Lara at long-on! That's the ninth wicket down!
fullish and on the off, driven to cover
Sreesanth manages to pinch a single
and another single, this time to Harbhajan, as he sweeps to square-leg, and India end their innings on 246 for 9 from 50 overs

inn2.comm: good length delivery outside the off stump, ball kept low after hitting the deck and Gayle is beaten outside the off stump
good length delivery outside the off stump, shaping away from the left-hander, Gayle watchfully leaves it through to the keeper
fuller length delivery outside the off stump, Gayle gets well forward, drops his wrists and defends it away towards short cover
drifting down the leg side, Gayle has a poke at it but makes no contact, rightly called a wide
pitched up and drifting down the leg side, once again Gayle fails to make contact, ball clips the pad and rolls down to short fine leg, easy single taken
good length delivery, angling across the right hander, Samuels watchfully leaves it through to the keeper
fulltoss to end the over, Samules strokes it away well wide of the fielder at mid-off and he will retain the strike
starts off with a good length delivery on the middle and off stump line, Samuels pushes forward and defends it straight back to the bowler

pitched up outside the off stump, hint of away swing, Samuels drives, opening the face of the bat and the ball races away towards third man, was in the air for sometime but the gully fielder was too square
bit wide and angling across, no shot offered
slightly short and angling across, Gayle watches it all the way into the keeper's gloves
another probing delivery outside the off stump, similar to the one that got rid of Gayle in the second match, Gayle shoulders arms and the ball thuds into the keeper's gloves
good length delivery outside the off stump, bit too wide and Gayle is not interested, Agarkar starts off with a decent over
good length delivery on the middle and off stump line, this one shaped back in a touch, Samuels covers the line nicely and strokes it back to the bowler
on the middle and leg stump line, turned away straight to the fielder at midwicket
good length delivery, the one that slants across the right hander, tempting delivery and Samuels has a poke at it, ball zips past the outside edge - well bowled Pathan.
drifting down the leg side, Samuels leaves it through to the keeper and pleading looks at the umpire, Asad Rauf too is not happy with the width
slower delivery, defended outside the off stump
short of a good length delivery outside the off stump, Gayle leans back and has a swat at it, not a well timed shot and the ball rolls away off the inner half of the bat
good length delivery on the stumps, shaping away a touch and Samuels drives it down to mid-on
driven away towards cover
good length delivery outside the off stump, driven away towards extra cover, Kaif there moves across quickly and cuts off the single
another good looking drive from Samuels but this time the ball goes straight to Kaif at extra cover
well bowled slower delivery, Samuels picks it up early and defends it down on the off side, well played in the end.
good length delivery outside the off stump, defended watchfully
drifting down the leg side
here we go!  good length delivery outside the off stump, was the slower delivery, Gayle picks it up early and drills it through extra cover for the first boundary of the innings, powerful shot
pitched up and drifting down the leg side, Gayle stays back, leans across a bit and jabs it away to the midwicket fence, wrong line and he takes full toll - Gayle style, Pathan under pressure here
good length delivery outside the off stump, hint of away swing, Gayle drives, opening the face of the bat and the ball rolls down to third man, easy single
steered down to third man
left alone outside the off stump
beaten! slower delivery outside the off stump, Gayle is beaten by the lack of pace and the ball rips past the outside edge, excellent ball to end the over
good length delivery on the middle and off stump line, defended straight back along the carpet and its picked up by Agarkar on his follow through

good length delivery outside the off stump, Samuels on the back-foot driving, nicely opens the face of the bat at the point of impact and gets it away behind point, Harbhajna hurtles across in the deep and keeps it down to just a single
excellent line and length, angling across the left-hander, Gayle moves forward and across and gets hit on the pad, loud appeal for lbw turned down, impact was outside the line of the off stump
nicely steered down to third man
played away well wide of the fielder at mid-on
defended on the back-foot, ball rolls away towards square leg
short of a good length delivery on the middle and leg stump line, Samuels stands tall on the back-foot and defends it down to silly mid-on
short and angling across, Samuels leans back and cuts hard, ball hits the ground hard and bounces over the fielder at gully - easy single and Gayle is back on srike.
short and wide outside the off stump, with Gayle at the other end you better forget it! Gayle comes down hard on it and the ball screams away to the backward point fence, no stopping that!
turned away straight to the fielder at square leg
good length delivery outside the off stump, driven hard but straight to Kaif at cover
defended watchfully
turned away off the pads to the square leg region
on the stumps, defended back to the bowler
Samuels too joins in, good length delivery outside the off stump and drive makes perfect contact, Sreesanth at mid-off is bit late off the blocks and the ball rockets away to the long-off fence
short of a good length delivery, defended down on the off side
another decent delivery, on the middle and off stump line, Samuels defends on the front-foot and the ball rolls away towards point

slower delivery on the middle and off stump line, Samuels stands tall on the back-foot and defends it down on the leg side, Agarkar on his follow through moves across quickly and negates the chance of a single
short and wide outside the off stump, driven off the back-foot and the gets it wide of the fielder at cover
better line and length, good length delivery on the stumps, defended watchfully
again on the stumps, Samuels gets right behind the line and defends it with a straight bat.
Sreesanth strays onto middle and leg, Samuels shuffles back and across and clips it away straight to Sehwag at midwicket
good length delivery outside the off stump, driven hard but straight to the fielder at extra cover, good over so far from Sreesanth

first-blood! good length delivery, pitched close to the off stump line and coming in with the angle, bit of a skidder - Samuels rocks back in an effort to whip it away through midwicket but fails to make contact and the ball hits him high on the pad, loud appeal and the dreaded finger goes up
worked away wide of mid-off
defended watchfully

another one! good length delivery, swinging in late and Morton is hit on the pad right in line with the stumps, loud appeal and umpire Bucknor brings up the slow finger of death - West Indies two down and in a spot of bother here
good length delivery, driven straight to the fielder at cover
short and wide outside the off stump, drive off the back-foot to the cover fence
driven straight to the fielder at mid-off, end of a successful over
full and outside the off stump, Gayle watches the ball carefully and leaves it alone to the keeper
down the leg side this time, left alone and a wide is called
left well alone outside the off stump
once again short of a good length and outside the off, left well alone to the keeper
fullish and on the stumps, inside edge onto pad, that tickle saved Gayle as a loud shout for the lbw goes up
short of a good length and on the off, defended
full and outside the off, driven firmly to mid off
short of a good length and outside the off stump, Sarwan goes back and cuts towards point, no chance of a run
full and on the stumps, driven to the on side
short of a good length and just outside the off, pushed to cover with an angled bat
just short of a driving length and on the off stump, punched to mid off
another fullish ball on the stumps, driven hard but straight to the fielder at cover, no chance of a run
short and wide, not so clever from Sreesanth, Sarwan goes back and across and cuts superbly through point
fuller this time and very straight, Sarwan drives back down the pitch but Sreesanth gets low and fields well in his followthrough
left well alone, this one goes through to the keeper
full and just outside the off stump, driven well but not past the man at mid off
full and on the off stump, defended to the off side with the full face of the bat
full and on the pads, flicked down to the man at fine-leg for a single
short of a good length and on the pads, flicked to the on side, off the pads towards square-leg
good-length ball on the off stump, driven towards long off for a single
fullish and outside the off stump, Sarwan goes for a big drive, the ball goes off the inside edge and runs away to the fine-leg fence
short of a driving length and outside the off stump, chopped towards point
overpitched, outside the off stump, Sarwan waits on the ball and drives beautifully through cover for a boundary
short of a good length and outside the off stumps, Sarwan angles the bat and plays the ball down to third-man for a single that brings up the fifty
short of a length and outside the off, once again Sarwan gets in good position and cuts well past the man at cover-point
just a bit too much width outside the off stump and a touch too short as well, Sarwan goes back and chops the ball down to third-man for a single
full and far outside the off, Gayle plonks his foot down the pitch and drives hard, off the outside edge down to third-man, not a convincing shot that
no ball called, fullish and on the stumps, Sarwan gets bat close to pad and defends watchfully
short and a bit of width, Sarwan this time fails to get hold of the cut and can only chop to the man at point
short of a length and outside the off, slapped to point
full and straight, well dug out to end the over
slower ball, cleverly bowled, Sarwan tries to guide it towards third-man but misses
full and on the off, defensive shot played and missed, shout for the lbw, turned down
full and slipping down the leg side, flick played and missed, the ball goes down towards short fine-leg, in comes the throw, just missed! That could have been close!
short and wide, that gets the treatment, Gayle goes back and smashes the ball to the point fence
too short, this one just sits up outside the off, Sarwan goes back and pulls magnificently, this one races to the fence in front of square
short of a length and outside the off, defended down towards third-man
short of a good length and outside the off, Gayle cuts down towards third-man
full and on the pads, Gayle flicks, it's in the air, Sehwag dives but cannot quite hold onto it at square-leg! That's a chance that really should have been taken. Could prove costly for India!
on the stumps, good length, defended away
full toss on the off stump, Gayle spots it early and drives with power and authority back past the bowler to the long-off boundary
middle and leg, fullish, tucked to square-leg
flat, slightly shorter, on the legs, flick played and missed, off the pad down towards fine-leg
tossed up a bit more, on the stumps, defended carefully to the off side
defended carefully once more
worked away to the leg side, easy single on offer here
flat and on the stumps, worked away to the on side, end of Harbhajan's first over
tossed up, on the middle and leg stump, spinning further down, played at and missed, wide called
and again! tossed up, on the middle and leg stump, spinning further down, played at and missed, wide called
short and a bit of width, cut down past point for a couple
fuller and straighter, defended carefully this time
tossed up nicely and on the stumps, Powar gets the batsman to drive, the ball bobs back down the pitch to the bowler
this one is maximum! Sarwan charges down the pitch, gets to the pitch of the ball and launches it into the stands over midwicket! That is a big hit!
and a defensive shot to end the over. Not the greatest start from Powar
arm ball on the stumps, defended at the last moment by Gayle
fuller, tossed up a touch, outside the off, defended towards the man at cover
full and outside the off, left alone to the keeper
flat and on the pads, sweep played and missed, hit on the pad, stifled lbw shout
fullish and on the off, driven to the off side, straight to mid off
full and once again on the pads, not the place to bowl, off the pads down to fine-leg
much better line and length, fullish and outside the off, a bit of drift and turn, defended carefully
Biggie! Sarwan once again waltzes down the pitch with lightning quick feet! He gets to the pitch of the ball and blasts it into the stands over long-on!
just slipping down leg, played at and missed
short of a length and on the stumps, worked away to the leg side
rank short ball from Powar, Sarwan goes back and pulls with some power, that boundary brings up his fifty! Well played!
short of a length and outside the off, steered down towards third-man for a single
driven to long-on
just short of a good length and outside the off, pushed past point for a single
on the pads and quite flat, worked away to the on side
flat and straight, defensive shot played, struck on the pad
just short of a length and outside the off, Sarwan goes back and pushes to cover
slightly short, driven wide of the fielder at cover
again Powar drags it short, on the middle and leg stump line, Sarwan gets behind the line and punches it down to long-on for a single
width offered outside the off stump, cut away straight to the fielder at point

take that! tossed up delivery, Gayle dances down the track, for a moment it looked like he got it wrong but no, he reaches out a bit and hammers it over the long-on fence, put that down as Gayle's contribution to the hole in the ozone layer - that was as big as it gets!
defended on the front-foot
driven down to long-off for an easy single
quicker delivery to start with, defended down on the off side
swept away well in front of square leg, easy single
turning in, Sarwan stays back and turns it away towards square leg
pitched on middle and leg and drifting down the leg side, Sarwan fails to make contact and the ball beats the keeper
tossed up outside the off stump, defended stretching well forward
pitched close to the off stump line and turning away, that creats the widht, Gayle leans back and cuts hard but fails to get it past the fielder at point
on the middle and off stump line, defended watchfully
good length delivery, coming in with the angle, Sarwan stays back and defends it down on the off side

another one, cutting in from outside the off stump, Sarwan on the back-foot defending and the ball rolls away behind the stumps on the off side, quick single called for, Dhoni moves across in a flash and scores a direct hit at the striker's end but Gayle comfortably makes his ground, third umpire confirms

got'm! that's the wicket they wanted! short of a good length delivery, pitched on middle and off and shaping away a touch, Gayle had no option but to play at it and the resultant edge goes straight to Dhoni behind the stumps - Agarkar with the all important breakthrough, West Indies three down.
good delivery first up, defended outside the off stump
good length delivery, close to the off stump line, Lara on the front-foot defending
wide outside the off stump, Lara has a poke at it and the ball goes past the outside edge, ball keeps low and Dhoni fails to collect it cleanly, four more added to the total
defended outside the off stump
cut away through point for a brace

ripper, quicker delivery, this one clipped the suface and turned in sharply, Sarwan goes back to cut and is almost beaten for pace, ball clips the inside edge and rolls away towards point, close call&

tossed up and turning in from wide outside the off stump, Sarwan gets behind the line and drives it away through extra cover, Lara call for the third and makes it across comfortablly, excellent running between the wickets
defended on the back-foot
good length delivery, cutting in from outside the off stump, driven away towards mid-off
another lovely delivery and Sarwan is beaten outside the off stump
slightly short but close to the off stump line, Sarwan leans back and cuts late, ball races away towards third man
slower delivery, on the stumps and Lara strokes it straight back down the track to the mid-on region
pitched up outside the off stump, in the slot and Lara drives hard, ball goes straight to the fielder at mid-off

good length delivery, pitched close to the off stump line and angling across, Lara gets well forward and taps it down to silly mid-off, played with soft hands and they scamper through for a single and that gets Lara off the mark
drifting down the leg side, Lara quickly goes down on one knee and sweeps it away to the fine leg fence, sort of a one handed sweep but the timing was perfect and the ball raced away to the fence
on the middle and off stump line, defended on the front-foot

beauty! tossed up on the middle and leg stump line, turning right across, Lara pushes forward - looking to work it away towards midwicket, ball turns across just enough to kiss the outside edge and goes straight to Dravid at first slip who takes it on the second attempt, big wicket and this match is back in the balance
tossed up and turning across, defended
played straight back down the track
fuller length delivery, driven back to the bowler
good length delivery, coming in with the angle and Sarwan drives it straight to the fielder at cover
close to the off stump line, steered down to third man for an easy single
fuller length delivery outside the off stump, punched down to mid-off
good length delivery outside the off stump, forced away towards cover
short and wide outside the off stump, ball kept low after hitting the deck and Chanderpaul who was looking to cut it way is beaten by a long way
on the middle and off stump line, driven back to the bowler, not a convincing shot and the ball came off the inner half of the bat

doosra! the one that turns away from the right-hander, Sarwan was clueless, pushes forward to defend and is beaten comprehensively, Dhoni collects the ball cleanly and whips off the bails in a flash, third umpire called in - green light flashes
off-spinner, the one that turns back in, Sarwan stays back and tucks it away through square leg for a single
slightly short, Chanderpaul takes it on the back-foot and punches it straight back to the bowler
quicker delivery outside the off stump, Chanderpaul goes back and across and taps it away behind point, no room for a single there
driven into the gap between cover and mid-off, Chanderpaul off the mark, about time too!
flatter trajectory, turning in from outside the off stump, Sarwan goes back and plays it away towards cover
good length delivery on the stumps, driven wide of the fielder at mid-on
good length delivery outside the off stump and Sarwan drives it away towards cover, excellent diving stop from Kaif saves runs
decent line and length, defended on the front-foot
short of a good length delivery, bit close to cut but Sarwan goes after it, ball zips past the outside edge, good over so far
slightly short and coming in with the angle, Sarwan stays back and steers it away behind point, Rain has a go at the striker's end stumps but fails to hit the target
driven wide of the cover fielder
starts off with a delivery drifting down the leg side, was there to be hit but Chanderpaul fails to make contact
fuller length delivery, turning across and Chanderpaul is squared-up, ball clips the outer half of the bat and rolls away towards short cover - well bowled
punched down to long-on, easy single added to the total
driven straight to the fielder at midwicket
Powar contines to struggle! hopeless long-hop, Sarwan rocks back and pulls it away to the midwicket fence, how convenient! there was protection in the deep but that man hardly got any time to react
nicely driven down to long-on for an easy single
good length delivery, no movement whatsoever, Sarwan nicely opens the face of the bat and steers it down to third man for a single

good length delivery, angling across the left-hander, Chanderpaul pushes forward and drives it away towards mid-off, Agarkar there moves across quickly but fails to stop it cleanly and the batsmen steal a single
good length delivery outside the off stump and Sarwan drives it away wide of the fielder at point
driven straight to the fielder at mid-off

good length delivery, pitched in line and angling across, Chanderpaul gets forward to the pitch of the delivery and drills it through the gap between mid-off and cover, hamstring or no-hamstring - that was a cracking shot!

four more! wounded, dangerous - it's all true I guess!  pitched up delivery outside the off stump, Sreesanth looking for some non-existent reverse swing there, Chanderpaul quickly gets into a good position and swats it past the fielder at mid-off who quickly gives up the chase
cut away off the back-foot, straight to Dravid at point
defended outside the off stump
flicked away off the pads to the square leg region
tossed up and turning in, driven down to long-off
driven hard and straight to Harbhajan at cover
played away towards cover
good length delivery on the middle and leg stump line, punched down to mid-on
on the pads, turned away well in front of square on the leg side
slightly short and angling across, no real width there, Sarwan leans back and cuts it away to third man for a single, played it late to get the placement right
drifting down the leg side, Chanderpaul shuffles across a long away, ball clips the pad and goes through to the keeper

shot! short and wide outside the off stump, Chanderpaul moves back and across and cuts it away to the third man fence, got right on top of the bounce and the ball just rocketed away off the meat of the bat, fielder in the deep had no chance of cutting it off, perfect timing and placement
defended outside the off stump
tossed up and on the off, flicked to midwicket, Kaif dives superbly and saves runs, good effort that
flat and on the stumps, defended
full and down the leg side, worked down to short fine-leg
tossed up beautifully and on the stumps, Sarwan can only push the ball back to the bowler, maiden over, well bowled that
full and slanting down the leg side, worked away through square-leg for a single
just short of a driving length, on the off, slanting away from the right-handed batsman, steered down to third-man for a single
full and straight, driven with the full face of the bat to wide mid-on
short one banged in, it barely gets up but the direction is good and Sarwan takes no chances and prefers to sway inside the line and leave the ball alone to the keeper
fullish and on the pads, worked to the leg side, Dravid fields at midwicket and has a throw at the stumps, narrow miss and that would have been close had it hit!
slower ball to end the over, full and straight, driven back to the bowler who bends low and fields
tossed up, on the stumps, Sarwan comes down the stumps and pads as he can't get to the pitch of the ball
slightly short, on the stumps, a bit of turn, pulled down through midwicket for a single
well tossed up and on the off, Chanderpaul uses his feet and drives inside out to cover
fired in quicker and on the pads, Sarwan waits on it and dabs through the on side for a single
quicker one, it's the arm ball, on the off, Chanderpaul reads it and defends watchfully, good bowling this
slightly shorter, outside the off, just the single, another good tidy over from Powar here
tossed up and on the off, Chanderpaul looks to come down the pitch and drive but can only push back to the bowler
flat once again and just on the off, defended carefully
quicker one on the stumps, Chanderpaul has to be content defending
driven off the back foot but not past the man at cover, four dot balls now
a touch shorter and on the pads, allows Chanderpaul to work the ball to the leg side for a single

fast, full, speared in on the pads, down leg side and all Sarwan needs to do is get bat to that. He manages and the ball races away to the fine-leg boundary ruining what would have been a fine over from Harbhajan
well flighted and on the leg stump, a bit of turn as the ball grips the surface, Chanderpaul defends to on
slightly short and on the stumps, pulled down to long-on
again a bit too short and this time it is Sarwan who works the ball down to long-on for a single
low full-toss outside the off, pushed past cover for a single
and a single to long-on to end the over, five came off it, West Indies picking odd the singles at the moment
slightly short and this allows Chanderpaul to rock back and pull the ball past Harbhajan towards long-on for a single
very full and quite straight, Sarwan gets the full face of the bat behind ball and defends to the bowler
flat again and quite full, defended to the on side with soft hands and a single is pinched
fullish and outside the off, steered wide of point with an angled bat for a single
flat and on the legs, clipped away towards square-leg for yet another single
again Chanderpaul cleverly picks off a single down to long off, five off the over
well flighted and on the pads, Chanderpaul works the ball through square-leg for a single
flatter and on the pads, Sarwan comes down the pitch anyhow and works a single to the leg side
tossed up and on the stumps, out comes the sweep, the ball goes down to long leg for a single
low full-toss on the leg stump, whipped away to the long-on region for a single
tossed up a bit more and slower, from round the stumps, the ball grips and turns, driven through the leg side for a single
yet another single to end the over, and West Indies are slowly but surely closing in on the target
flat and on the pads, clipped down to short fine-leg
worked past short fine-leg this time for an easy single, there is cover on the fence
flat and on the pads, Chanderpaul walks across his stumps and flicks well through square-leg
and another dab! single pinched as the ball is worked away towards square-leg
well flighted and on the off, Chanderpaul reaches for that a touch but is able to ease the ball down towards long off for a single
flat and quick to end his spell, defended back down the pitch. That is the end of Harbhajan's 10 overs and he has done well, conceding just 33 and picking up the vital wicket of Brian Lara
flat and on the pads, lapped round the corner to long leg
flatter and quicker, a touch short though and punched down to long off for a single
held back a touch, good dip in the air for Powar, Sarwan comes down the pitch and defends to on
flatter and on the legs, eased to long-on for another single
flighted and outside the off, Chanderpaul drives, the ball streaks away off the outside edge to short third-man
down the pitch and driven to long off, single to end Powar's spell. He ends with 59 runs from 10 overs, a good comeback after his first 3 overs went for 31
fullish and on the stumps, Chanderpaul goes for the big hit. He's not to the pitch of the ball but he goes through with the shot and even one handed the ball sails over the ropes at long-on!
full and on the stumps, no-ball, defended back to the bowler
short of a good length and on the off, whipped to the on side for a single
fullish and outside the off, eased wide of long off for a single
full and just outside the off, Chanderpaul jams the bat down and gets the ball through point for a single
worked away down towards third-man for a single
and a single to end the over, that makes it twelve off the over and West Indies are narrowing the gap and should walk home with ease
flat and a touch short, Chanderpaul waits on the ball and plays a cute paddle sweep, that goes very fine and Chanderpaul gets to fifty!
short of a good length and on the off, pulled down the pitch, Sehwag dives and fields
eased down to long-on for a single
worked to the leg side, quick couple scampered
just short of a length and outside the off, Sarwan opens the face of the bat and plays the ball very very late, that races away to the fence and Sarwan gets to 98
driven through square-leg, quick couple scampered, Sarwan gets to hundred! His first against India and a tremendous knock! The crowd erupts in celebration!
full and on the off, driven inside out to mid off
fullish and just a touch outside the off, Chanderpaul plays it carefully back to the bowler
fullish once more and on the off, hit to mid off, Harbhajan fields and has a shy, that would have been very close if the throw had hit!
low full-toss on the off, punched to the leg side
slightly full and a bit of width outside the off, driven inside out through cover but just a single
full, fast, just outside the off, Chanderpaul walks across and flicks beautifully through square-leg for a single
short one banged in, that is a poor delivery, a half-tracker, pulled well, Pathan runs around and fields really well on the roped, saved a certain boundary
low full-toss on the stumps, driven inside out just wide of long off for a single
down the pitch and driven well, the ball goes past the bowler and Robin Uthappa fielding at long-on has to slide to save that
just short of a good length and outside the off, Sarwan gives himself a bit of room and jams the ball down to third-man
full, outside the off, from round the stumps, Chanderpaul flashes at that, the ball goes off a thick outside edge down to the third-man fence! Four crucial runs and surely now West Indies are home!
slower ball to end the over, angled down towards point, no run off it, 10 runs from this over
full and very straight, not a bad ball at all but Sarwan tackles it superbly flicking the ball through the on side for a single

Pathan goes for the yorker, it's a touch too full, Chanderpaul looks to flick, misses and is hit on the pad, loud shout and it's upheld! Chanderpaul is gone for 58 but it might just be a case of too little too late from India. Just 9 runs needed for victory now.
down the leg side, that is a bad ball, wide called. That's not what you should be bowling in the death in a tight game
slower ball, Bravo gets a taste of his own medicine, played at and missed, rapped on the pad, shout for the lbw, turned down, rightly so, that pitched outside leg
full and on the pads, whipped well through the on side
fullish and outside the off, driven to point, no run there and seven needed off seven
short ball, it sits up a touch and Sarwan dabs the ball down to third-man for a single, that hung in the air for a bit but fell well short of the man at third-man

RUN OUT! Can you believe it? A full ball outside the off, driven inside out through cover, Pathan fields on the ropes and throws the ball in. Sarwan calls for the second, then changes his mind and it's a big mix-up! Not over yet apparently ...
low full toss just outside the off stump, driven at and missed, through to the keeper
fullish and on the off, driven inside out through cover, now 4 needed off 3 balls
full and on the off, driven inside out to cover, Dravid misfields! Two given away instead of one and that is a costly miss. Sarwan is back on strike now
FOUR! That's it! Sreesanth goes for the yorker and it's just a touch too full, Sarwan gives himself a bit of room and clobbers the ball through cover for a boundary that seals India's fate!
